      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup by a second analyst; boundary conditions and loading verified against ASTM F1717 test protocol.",
      "rationale": "A second credentialed FEA analyst independently reviewed boundary condition application, material property assignment, and contact definitions. Discrepancies were resolved prior to production runs. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic continuum model with frictional contact is appropriate for predicting stiffness and yield force under monotonic quasi-static compression-bending; model form justified by literature and prior FDA studies.",
      "rationale": "The pedicle screw construct is modeled as a linear elastic titanium alloy assembly with frictional contact at the screw-rod interface. Bilinear kinematic hardening is applied for yield prediction. Model form is consistent with published FDA and industry practice for F1717 simulation. Required level 3 is met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties (Ti-6Al-4V: E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa) sourced from ASTM F136 and measured lot certificates; geometry from CAD nominal with dimensional inspection confirmation.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus and yield strength were taken from the device manufacturer's material certificates for the tested lot, consistent with ASTM F136 Grade 23. Geometric dimensions were verified against CMM inspection reports for three representative screws. Uncertainty in inputs is quantified and propagated. Required level 3 is met."
    },
    {
