      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the clinical failure modes of pedicle screw constructs under compression-bending.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the spine; yield force and force at 40 mm are directly related to fatigue life and fracture risk. These QoIs are endorsed by FDA guidance and the published literature as the most clinically relevant metrics for F1717 assessment. Required level 3 is met."
