    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted because the ASTM F1717 protocol is a standardized, industry-wide benchmark with strong regulatory precedent, and multi-laboratory replication at N=11 provides sufficient confidence in test reproducibility. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds across all three independent modeling environments. The overall credibility evidence supports the decision to accept the FEA model for its intended use in the submission.",
